<div class="recipe">
<p>Also known as a crumble, this dessert will bring you back to a simpler time. The sweet pie-like filling, the cinnamony, crispy oat topping, and a rich vanilla ice cream show how simple it is to make something that tastes like a work of art. If you were lucky enough to grow up with a Grandma that made this for you (which we did, and this is her recipe), then we'll be happy to take you back to those years with this dish. If not, well, prepare to be the one that passes this down to your family.</p>
<p>Crisp tends to be the forgotten sibling of pie, but honestly, we prefer the crisp where we come from. There is just something special that happens within the topping that takes it over the edge.</p>
<p>Serving this hot with ice cream is an absolute necessity. As the sweet cream melts into the dessert below, it elevates the whole experience.</p>   
<br>
