<br>

<div class="ingredients">
    <h3><strong>Ingredients</strong></h3>
    <strong>Filling:</strong>
    <ul>
        <li>1 1/2 pounds of fruit (we are doing apples thinly sliced, but almost anything will work here. You can even use frozen fruit if you find that easier)</li>
        <li>1/4 - 1/2 cup granluated sugar (use more or less sugar depending on your taste) </li>
        <li>1/4 cup all purpose flour</li>
        <li>1/2 tablespoon cinnamon</li>
    </ul>
    <strong>Topping:</strong>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup all purpose flour</li>
        <li>3/4 cup packed brown sugar</li>
        <li>3/4 cup rolled oats</li>
        <li>1/2 cup butter, melted</li>
    </ul>

    <h3><strong>Directions</strong></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Preheat oven to 375F and lightly grease a baking pan. Any pan should work, but you will want at least an inch of fruit filling covering the bottom.</li>
        <li>Filling: In a large bowl, toss the fruit, sugar, flour, and cinnamon together. Transfer into the prepared baking dish and spread it out into an even layer.</li>
        <li>Topping: Toss together the flour, brown sugar, and oats together. Drizzle in the melted butter. Mix well, it should have the consistency of wet sand. Sprinkle over the filling.</li>
        <li>Bake for 30 minutes, or until the topping is golden brown and the filling is bubbling beneath it. Enjoy!</li>
    </ol>
</div>
</div>





